The paper presents a language for finite state continuous time Bayesian networks, which are used to model structured stochastic processes that evolve over continuous time. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SI), information theory (cs.IT), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
